    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Monkey Oligopeptide-1 Amide Acetate is the acetate salt of a single chain peptide produced synthetically to be identical to a portion of the protein, Rhesus Theta Defensin-1/2 Subunit B, which is found in the monkey. The peptide contains a maximum of 76 amino acids consisting of arginine, cysteine, glycine, leucine and valine, in which the C-terminus is an amide. The protein consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
